b'@mileyqueenley It is CrAzY how many places I have yet to perform! I am going to get creative on ways that in the meantime I can deliver to you what you deserve in exchange for your support! I love you dearly!'

b'@mileyqueenley NOW speaking to my international fans! \nI realize how upsetting this feels but I promise I will provide content and performances for my fans to look forward to\xe2\x80\xa6.. I have recently made big changes surrounding my career and a very important factor for doing so was YOU!'
b'@mileyqueenley there are already so many iconic clubs at risk.'

b'@mileyqueenley I also want to keep live music relevant for the artists with smaller platforms than I have or are in different stages of their career. Performing live is how they provide for themselves. I don\xe2\x80\x99t want small concert venues to go extinct (which is why I joined Save the stages)'

b'@mileyqueenley to put myself in a position to be ridiculed note for note LIVE for 90 minutes. As a singer who prides myself on singing LIVE , mistakes are bound to happen and it makes me feel way to much pressure to be pitch perfect which takes away from my focus on the crowd in front of me.'

b'@mileyqueenley Now speaking as the performer, making a mistake live is an inevitable part of the show!It creates an \xe2\x80\x9cin the moment\xe2\x80\x9c experience that makes a song different from the record that\xe2\x80\x99s been played on repeat by the fans! But with social media\xe2\x80\x99s harsh criticism to be honest I don\xe2\x80\x99t want-'

b'@mileyqueenley The divide in this world is usually so deep that by being in a space for a few hours where everyone has one common interest ( the artist they came to see ) it\xe2\x80\x99s a beautifully unique thing!'

b'@mileyqueenley There is a discomfort to live concerts \xe2\x80\xa6. Waiting in long lines to enter the venue or get merchandise & in doing that there is also a connection with other fans and audience members.'

b'@mileyqueenley I shared a story on Stern speaking only from my own up bringing that when I wanted to go see a show it fueled my fire to work hard so I could go with my friends to see our favorite act! \n\nThat is a small part of the steps I am talking about that gets you to the gig!'

b'@mileyqueenley Live concerts are ritualistic. There is a timeless process that I want to honor by keeping my live show experience exclusive to the \xe2\x80\x9caudience of the night\xe2\x80\x9d.  I believe in the power of live music staying a one of a kind intimate experience.'

b'@mileyqueenley I never want to disappoint my fans. I hope my appreciation of your support and loyalty is clear! If it wasn\xe2\x80\x99t when I was discussing my decision to not live stream upcoming concerts here is some clarity.'
